  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).",
    "Season chicken with salt and pepper.",
    "Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken pieces and cook until golden brown on both sides, about 6 minutes per side.",
    "Remove chicken from the skillet and set aside. Add celery to the same skillet and sauté for 2-3 minutes or until slightly softened.",
    "Add onions and garlic to the skillet and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Return chicken to the skillet with onions and garlic. Stir in soy sauce, lime juice, mayonnaise, ginger, salt, pepper, chili flakes, and sesame seeds. Cook for another 10-15 minutes or until fully heated through and slightly thickened.",
    "Serve hot as a main dish."
  ],
